The spiral is the usual “Ulam” spiral:

* 1 is at \((0,0)\);
* the numbers increase to the right, then go upward, left, down, …

For a point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
k=\max(|x|,|y|) \qquad\text{(the “layer’’)}
\]

The biggest number in layer \(k\) is  

\[
M_k=(2k+1)^2
\]

and it is located at the bottom‑right corner \((k,-k)\).

Going counter‑clockwise from that corner we have  

* bottom side \((y=-k)\): offset \(=k-x\)  
* left side   \((x=-k)\): offset \(=2k+(y+k)\)  
* top side    \((y= k)\): offset \(=4k+(x+k)\)  
* right side  \((x= k)\): offset \(=6k+(k-y)\)

The number at \((x,y)\) is  

\[
n=M_k-\text{offset}.
\]

---

### 1.  Locate 2026

\[
\sqrt{2026}=45.0\ldots\quad\Longrightarrow\quad
m=47\;(=2k+1),\;k=23,\;M_{23}=47^{2}=2209.
\]

\[
\text{offset}=M_{23}-2026=183.
\]

Since \(2k=46\),

\[
138\le 183<184 \Longrightarrow\text{right side, }
\text{offset}_4=183-138=45.
\]

Hence  

\[
(2026)=(x,y)=(k,\;k-\text{offset}_4)=(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  The eight neighbours

| neighbour | \((x,y)\) | layer \(k\) | side | offset | number \(n=M_k-\text{offset}\) |
|-----------|----------|-------------|------|--------|--------------------------------|
| (22,‑23) | (22,‑23) | 23 | bottom | \(k-x=1\) | \(2209-1=2208\) |
| (23,‑23) | (23,‑23) | 23 | bottom | \(k-x=0\) | \(2209\) |
| (24,‑23) | (24,‑23) | 24 | right  | \(3\cdot48+(24-(-23))=191\) | \(2401-191=2210\) |
| (22,‑22) | (22,‑22) | 22 | bottom | \(0\) | \(45^{2}=2025\) |
| (24,‑22) | (24,‑22) | 24 | right  | \(3\cdot48+(24-(-22))=190\) | \(2401-190=2211\) |
| (22,‑21) | (22,‑21) | 22 | right  | \(3\cdot44+(22-(-21))=175\) | \(2025-175=1850\) |
| (23,‑21) | (23,‑21) | 23 | right  | \(3\cdot46+(23-(-21))=182\) | \(2209-182=2027\) |
| (24,‑21) | (24,‑21) | 24 | right  | \(3\cdot48+(24-(-21))=189\) | \(2401-189=2212\) |

---

### 3.  Sum of the neighbours

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum}&=2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212\\
&=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
